        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(gateway): add agent.capabilities method",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Adds `agent.capabilities` gateway method (READ scope) returning a structured summary of what an agent is configured to do\n- Response includes: resolved primary model and fallbacks, tool count by source (core vs plugin), configured MCP server names, active skills, bound channel IDs from bindings, and active session count\n- Aggregates from existing utilities: `buildToolsCatalogResult`, `normalizeConfiguredMcpServers`, `resolveAgentEffectiveModelPrimary`, `listConfiguredBindings`, and the combined session store\n- Addresses the discoverability gap: operators can inspect what an agent is actually set up to do without reading raw config\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [ ] `agent.capabilities` returns correct model for default agent\n- [ ] Tool count matches `tools.catalog` result for same agent\n- [ ] MCP server names reflect `cfg.mcp.servers` config\n- [ ] Channels list reflects bindings targeting the agent\n- [ ] READ scope enforced\n- [ ] `pnpm check:changed` passes\n\nThanks @ioodu",
